body:
I've added a macro to `Illuminate\Testing\TestResponse` which I'm unable to call because pest throws a `ReflectionException`.

```
  1   vendor/pestphp/pest/src/Support/Reflection.php:30
      ReflectionClass::getMethod("assertMatchesHtmlSnapshot")

  2   vendor/pestphp/pest/src/Support/HigherOrderMessage.php:74
      Pest\Support\Reflection::call(Object(Illuminate\Testing\TestResponse), "assertMatchesHtmlSnapshot", [])

  3   vendor/pestphp/pest/src/Support/HigherOrderMessageCollection.php:33
      Pest\Support\HigherOrderMessage::call(Object(Illuminate\Testing\TestResponse))
```

I was able to fix it by adding a `try-catch` to the `Reflection::call()` method, check if `__call` exists and if so pass method call to overloaded `__call`.

```php
public static function call(object $object, string $method, array $args = [])
{
    $reflectionClass = new ReflectionClass($object);

    try {
        $reflectionMethod = $reflectionClass->getMethod($method);

        $reflectionMethod->setAccessible(true);

        return $reflectionMethod->invoke($object, ...$args);
    } catch(ReflectionException $ex) {
        if (method_exists($object, '__call')) {
            return $object->__call($method, $args);
        }

        throw $ex;
    }
}
```

